                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    A SIPP (Self-Invested Personal Pension) is a type of UK
                    personal pension that gives you control over how your
                    retirement savings are invested. You can choose from a wide
                    range of assets (funds, shares, ETFs, investment trusts and
                    more), within a tax‑advantaged wrapper. Contributions
                    normally receive tax relief, and investments grow free of UK
                    income and capital gains tax inside the SIPP.
                  </p>
                </details>
                <details class="border rounded-md p-3">
